@startuml
' ============================================================
' Diagram   : Nondisruptive Service Relocation - Runtime Flow
' Section   : 14.4 Nondisruptive Service Relocation Architecture
' Type      : Sequence diagram
' Message   : A duplicate cloud service is confirmed to be
'             receiving requests successfully BEFORE the
'             original is deactivated, ensuring zero
'             disruption to consumers.
' ============================================================

!include ../../../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/interaction/sequence-diagram-style.iuml

title 14.4 Nondisruptive Service Relocation\nDuplicate-then-Cutover Sequence

skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #F0F4F8
skinparam ActorBorderColor #4A6B8A
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF8DC
skinparam noteBorderColor #999999

actor "Cloud Service\nConsumers" as CSC
participant "Automated\nScaling Listener" as ASL
participant "Cloud Service A\non VS A\n(Physical Server A)" as CSA
participant "VIM" as VIM
participant "Live VM\nMigration" as LVM
participant "Origin\nHypervisor" as HO
participant "Destination\nHypervisor" as HD
participant "Cloud Service A\non VS B\n(Physical Server B)" as CSB

== Steady state ==
CSC -> ASL : 1. requests
ASL -> CSA : forward

== Trigger ==
CSA -> ASL : 2. workload reaches\npredefined threshold
ASL -> VIM : 3. signal relocation

== Provision destination ==
VIM -> LVM : 4. initiate live VM migration
LVM -> HO : instruct origin
LVM -> HD : 5. create duplicate VS\n& cloud service
HD -> CSB : start

== Synchronize ==
CSA <-> CSB : 6. synchronize state

== Cut-over (only after success confirmed) ==
ASL -> CSB : redirect
CSC -> CSB : 8. requests succeed
note right of CSB
  Removal proceeds only after
  consumer requests are confirmed
  to be successfully exchanged
  with the new instance.
end note
HO -> CSA : 7. remove instance

note over LVM
  Migration mode A: copy VS disks
   when source uses local or non-shared remote storage.
  Migration mode B: transfer ownership only
   when source and destination share remote storage.
end note

note over VIM
  Mechanisms: automated scaling listener, load balancer,
  cloud storage device, hypervisor, virtual server,
  cloud usage monitor, pay-per-use monitor,
  resource replication, SLA management system, SLA monitor.
  CONFLICT: cannot combine with the direct I/O access
  architecture (Chapter 15).
end note

@enduml

